sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM configurations 
WHERE is_active = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM actions
WHERE UNICODE(action_name) > 70;

SELECT action_name, description
FROM actions
WHERE action_id > 5;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM actions
WHERE is_active = 1 AND action_id NOT IN (SELECT action_id FROM documentation);

SELECT user_id, COUNT(*) AS dock_count 
FROM user_activity 
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT a.action_id) AS total_actions_with_docs
FROM actions a
JOIN documentation d ON a.action_id = d.action_id;

external_knowledge:
- In this context, 'explorers' metaphorically refer to the 'users'.;
- 'Set foot in the vast wilderness of our digital realm' means engaging in activities recorded in the system.;
- 'Unique trails' symbolize distinct actions performed by users, represented by `action_id`.;

sql:
SELECT user_id, activity_type, activity_date
FROM user_activity
WHERE action_id IN (SELECT action_id FROM documentation);

external_knowledge:
- "actions" represent the different types of actions or tasks in the system;
- "configurations" represent different ways these actions are set up;
- "parameters" are the inputs required for these actions, with "mandatory" meaning they are necessary for the action to execute;
- "options" are the choices available for parameters, and "default" indicates a pre-set choice;
- "vibrant actions" and "bouquets" are metaphors for active actions and configurations respectively;
- "essential petal" refers to a required parameter that has a default option (pre-set color);
- "average" in the context of configurations means the mean number of configurations across all actions.
